  "prompt": "What is the best Italian restaurant in Seattle?",
  "response": "Seattle has a vibrant dining scene with several excellent Italian restaurants. While \"best\" can be subjective and depends on personal preferences, some highly regarded options include:\n\n1. **Canlis** - A fine dining institution that offers a contemporary take on Italian cuisine, with stunning views and an exceptional wine list.\n2. **Spinasse** - Known for its homemade pasta and traditional Northern Italian dishes, Spinasse is a favorite for its authentic flavors and cozy atmosphere.\n3. **Il Corvo** - Renowned for its fresh pasta and simple, delicious sauces, Il Corvo is a casual spot that focuses on high-quality ingredients.\n4. **Pike Place Market's Barolo** - Offers rustic cuisine in a lively setting, highlighting the flavors of Northern Italy.\n5. **Cafe Campagne** - A bistro-style restaurant focusing on French but with some Italian influences, it\u2019s well-loved for its ambiance and seasonal offerings.\n\nIt\u2019s always a good idea to check recent reviews and make reservations, as the dining scene can change frequently!",
